      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Quite a few hopes here over the short course. Siding with NORMANDY LASS (5) who ran a strong race first up in a handy little race at Caulfield Heath, beaten a head on that occasion. She's got a good overall record and should come on from that having been in great form at the end of last campaign. She'll land on speed and go close. BLUE HOTEL (7) resumes. Her form last time in doesn't read all that well but she took on some of the top fillies including My Gladiola. The listed win on debut as a 2yo says she's right up to this. EGERTON (2) is a bit up and down but was good last time at Caulfield Heath and will be the one looking to flash over the top. PETIT ARTISTE (8) struggled second up in a tougher race but had been good fresh and this suits. TUSCALOOSA GEM (9) next best.",
